O God! Thou art my God alone;
No rival shade eclipses Thee.
In midnight hush, my soul has known
Thy voice that sings eternally.
I wander far on trembling feet,
Yet always turn to find Thee near;
In bread and breath, in hope and heat—
Thy presence silences my fear.
O God! Thou art my God alone;
In every dawn, my heart makes clear.
